Extraordinary movie about two legends of Argentine Tango. "The life and love story of Argentina's famous tango dancers Maria Nieves Rego and Juan Carlos Copes, who met as teenagers and danced together for nearly fifty years until a painful separation tore them apart", who are still dancing separately, today. It is Argentina's Oscar nominee. Through in personal interviews, recreations of moments in their lives and archival footage we come to know their passions, heartbreaks, personal joys, tragedies, bitterness and personal joys.
amazing story of an amazing woman, a must see for all Tango fans
Vrey interesting movie. Every Argentinian Tango lover MUST see it. This is the spirit of that dance .
I enjoyed this story very much. It brought a lot of great memories back to us.

Beautifully made movie, with the actual people talking to the actors that played them in different eras. There is a lot of subtle symbolism, and one needs to watch the movie a few times to get all of it.
